flowRoot.flowPara: Initial short list shows common locales.
Show more expands the list to show all languages.
Search bar is shown for the expanded list. Search filters the language list only (does not return locales).
Languages without regional variants can be seleted directly from the language list. Languages with more than one region show an arrow for navigating to a sub-list.
Top of the list shows installed languages, with the current locale as row one.
Additional resources are required to provide complete French language coverage. They can be downloaded later if you don't want to do it now.
If a language is selected that has missing flatpak extensions:
* If online and auto-update is on, automatically download them (show progress in the panel)
* Otherwise, show a message dialog to ask what to do:
If No Thanks is selected, the dialog closes and the prompt is shown to restart to use the new language.
If download is selected, download progress is shown in the panel.
